Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Brookdale Avenue and Seventh Street West

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 300 Brookdale Avenue and 730 Seventh Street West, Cornwall, ON is an exceptionally well-located redevelopment site, with the potential to build a mixed-used offering in one of Cornwall’s most active and development forward areas. Consisting of a large parcel of land approximately 45.205 acres with over 2,500 feet of frontage along one of Cornwall’s busiest thoroughfares in the central-west part of the City, the Property offers an incoming developer an excellent opportunity to make a big statement in one of Ontario’s gateway communities. Immediately to the south of the Property is the International Border to the United States and the new Seaway International Bridge crossing the St. Lawrence River. To the east of the Property, opposite Brookdale Avenue are additional commercial uses and older residential. To the west of the subject Property is a large recreational arena (Benson Center), and vacant land. The Property is currently zoned MFR:20: Manufacturing 20. This is an industrial zone permitting various light to medium manufacturing and warehousing uses. However, there will be tremendous support from the City of Cornwall to re-zone the Property to other uses.
